    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860h.9111 RR/7–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 462<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in <persName corresp="#p_Y1">Yugoslavia</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SH2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">plain</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-11">July 11,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>261. …</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Borba</hi> sharply criticizes Reuters for attitude of
                    “protectionism” and “inclination contrary to fact” in favor of Greeks during
                    Yugoslav-Greek dispute on treatment of Macedonians in north <persName
                        corresp="#p_G4">Greece</persName>. Editorialist denies charge of Reuters
                    editor that <persName corresp="#p_Y1">Yugoslavia</persName> wishes to make
                    territorial claims on <persName corresp="#p_G4">Greece</persName> and hence
                    press campaign by pointing out alleged expansionist ambitions of Greek
                    chauvinist officials. He admits that Yugoslavs and “all true democrats” are <pb
                        facs="0812" n="680" xml:id="pg_680"/> against Athens Government and that
                        <persName corresp="#p_Y1">Yugoslavia</persName> hopes question of Greek
                    misrule in Macedonia will be subject of “international forum” if not Big Three
                    Conference.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
